.TH "sata_std_hardreset" 9 "sata_std_hardreset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sata_std_hardreset \- COMRESET w/o waiting or classification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sata_std_hardreset
.BI "(struct ata_link *link "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *class "  ","
.BI "unsigned long deadline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
link to reset
.IP "class" 12
resulting class of attached device
.IP "deadline" 12
deadline jiffies for the operation

Standard SATA COMRESET w/o waiting or classification.

LOCKING:
Kernel thread context (may sleep)
.SH "RETURN"
0 if link offline, -EAGAIN if link online, -errno on errors.
